===Etymology===
{{etyl|xno}}, from Old Northern French ''[[wage]]'', a northern variant of {{etyl|fro}} ''[[gauge]]'', [[gage]], from {{etyl|frk}} ''*waddi, wadja'' (cognate with {{etyl|ang|-}} ''[[wedd]]''), from {{proto|Germanic|wadjo, wadi-|pledge|lang=}} from {{proto|Indo-European|wadh-|to pledge, redeem a pledge|lang=}}. Akin to {{etyl|non|-}} ''[[veþja]]'' "to pledge", {{etyl|got|-}} ''wadi''. More at [[wed]].

